data.name: label23.Text
data.value: This will run the calibration routine of the Mechaduino. The Motor will step trough every fullstep 3 times and records the encoder readings. It will run trough all steps one more time to check the readings. At the end it will post the lookuptable that needs to copied to the lookup_table.cpp file.

data.name: label27.Text
data.value: Here you can find the extra pin settings. If "Use anble Pin" is ticked the motor can only be enabled trough the defined pin in board.h (pin D3 as default). If "Invert Direction" is ticked the interpretation of the direction pin state will be switched.

data.name: label26.Text
data.value: Here are the motor settings collected. The rated torque and rated current are specific for your motor. The rated current is the current the motor deliveres the rated torque. The current is the maximal current the Mechaduino will deliver to the motor.

data.name: label25.Text
data.value: This settings are depending on the motor you're using. The Fullsteps are usualy 200 or 400. Microstepping is a interpolation between these Fullsteps. Microstepping must be between 1 and 128 and a power of 2 aswell.

data.name: label21.Text
data.value: Tunes the PID Controller of the Meachaduino. Insert the number of cycles and klick run. The Autotune will run the number of cycles and average the calculated parameters. Returns rough settings for the controller Tuned parameters: Kp, Ki, Kd
